---
import ChapterLabel from "./ChapterLabel.astro";
---

<section
	id="the-problem"
	class="bg-[var(--color-bg-dark)] px-6 py-16 sm:py-[var(--spacing-section-y)]"
	aria-labelledby="the-problem-title"
>
	<div class="mx-auto max-w-[var(--width-content)]">
		<!-- Separator -->
		<hr class="mb-16 border-[var(--color-border-dark)] sm:mb-24" aria-hidden="true" />

		<ChapterLabel title="The Problem" dark id="the-problem-title" />

		<p
			class="animate-on-scroll stagger-1 max-w-[var(--width-paragraph)] font-[var(--font-body)] text-lg leading-[1.7] text-[var(--color-text-light)]"
		>
			The energy grid is undergoing the most dramatic transformation since electrification.
			Renewables, electric vehicles, distributed generation, and extreme weather are reshaping
			demand patterns faster than traditional forecasting methods can follow.
		</p>

		<p
			class="animate-on-scroll stagger-2 mt-6 max-w-[var(--width-paragraph)] font-[var(--font-body)] text-lg leading-[1.7] text-[var(--color-text-muted-light)]"
		>
			Legacy statistical models were built for a predictable grid. They assume stable demand
			curves, seasonal patterns, and incremental change. But the grid of 2026 doesn't work that
			way. Forecast errors cascade into grid instability, wasted capacity, and billions in
			economic loss.
		</p>

		<!-- Pull quote -->
		<blockquote
			class="animate-on-scroll stagger-3 mt-12 max-w-[640px] border-l-[3px] border-[var(--color-accent)] py-2 pl-6"
		>
			<p
				class="font-[var(--font-display)] text-xl italic leading-[1.4] text-[var(--color-accent)] sm:text-[28px]"
			>
				Forecast errors don't just cost money — they destabilize the infrastructure that modern
				life depends on.
			</p>
		</blockquote>

		<!-- Accuracy comparison (dark variant) -->
		<div class="animate-on-scroll mt-12">
			<div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
				<!-- Traditional methods -->
				<div class="rounded-[var(--radius-card)] border border-[var(--color-border-dark)] p-6">
					<p
						class="font-[var(--font-body)] text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.05em] text-[var(--color-text-muted-light)]"
					>
						Traditional Statistical Methods
					</p>
					<p
						class="mt-3 font-[var(--font-mono)] text-[32px] font-bold leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.02em] text-[var(--color-text-light)] sm:text-[48px]"
					>
						MAPE: 4.2%
					</p>
					<p class="mt-2 font-[var(--font-body)] text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted-light)]">
						Industry baseline (ARIMA, exponential smoothing)
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- GridForesight ML -->
				<div
					class="rounded-[var(--radius-card)] border border-[var(--color-border-dark)] border-l-[3px] border-l-[var(--color-accent)] p-6 shadow-lg shadow-black/20"
				>
					<p
						class="font-[var(--font-body)] text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.05em] text-[var(--color-text-muted-light)]"
					>
						GridForesight ML Models
					</p>
					<p
						class="mt-3 font-[var(--font-mono)] text-[32px] font-bold leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.02em] text-[var(--color-text-light)] sm:text-[48px]"
					>
						MAPE: 2.1%
					</p>
					<p class="mt-2 font-[var(--font-body)] text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted-light)]">
						Trained on Grid Foresight Lab research
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<p
				class="mt-6 font-[var(--font-body)] text-base font-semibold text-[var(--color-accent)]"
			>
				50% reduction in forecast error, validated on real grid data
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
